^{The primary nerve involved in the erection process, the dorsal penile nerve, is a branch of the pudendal nerve. The pudendal nerve is a major nerve extending from the base of the spine to the external genitalia and is involved in a number of physiological and pathological processes. Trauma to the pelvic region, especially involving the pudendal nerve, can cause erectile dysfunction (Rogers, 2003).}
